<normalizedToken id="9B61F0898EBA307B22B6897A18AD12EB" originalValue="praténsis" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">pratensis</normalizedToken>
Dierbach
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA44478B448BD23394052FB34B83CDA6" pageId="null" pageNumber="330" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="CAF834B8BE4C95B8876F891411D57ADC" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Wiesen-Baldrian</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="D0989D85D7C26E217C3974687579BDD3" pageId="null" pageNumber="330" type="description">
<paragraph id="9AE6FD49175B67195EC46AE9424DDFDB" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="C0783A4A491D9F34B856219EA69505E0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Valeriana" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="null" pageNumber="330" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="collina">
<emphasis id="DC87B464BDE520546703F4C54A64990F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">V. collina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 8c) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="9316ABB82AA8E05160DE7FCE9B615DFE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">
Stengel kahl; mittlere 
<normalizedToken id="C940C7FA20C2885D6520D2949B840DD3" originalValue="Stengelblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Stengelblaetter</normalizedToken>
unterseits kahl oder mit 0,2
</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="52FB3B447D7B3DC984EF4AF7FAA96548" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">0,5 mm langen</emphasis>
, 
<normalizedToken id="9297B594FC4C8B251CEC37F4A40F8599" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">+/-</normalizedToken>
<emphasis id="E9BB20534C91B4F32FB711DE321D33AE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">anliegenden Haaren.</emphasis>
- 
<normalizedToken id="66C0E384A8A93952110A4163EC0CFA14" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="CC964884F1BCF656F821256D0A4B729C" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="EE9B6879C0A1770A5F8F4618FFB204A3" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="5D13F6D0B1A033440FB169436EF0356C" originalValue="früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">frueher</normalizedToken>
Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A2622766E0722B9505F8B7E44BA4003" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis id="E28FBA9B9BCDE00F05979659289D0A97" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Zytologische Angaben.</emphasis>
Keine Untersuchungen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D069BE35E8BDBCD96A340B4E1792B743" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis id="41BD7F9EDBE793ABB2F5C0D584A7FEAB" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin. Feuchte oder wechselfeuchte, lockere 
<normalizedToken id="17CA8FE3F546D9C323633D55CD5A3AFA" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Boeden</normalizedToken>
in 
<normalizedToken id="D71AB7BEE8E46DE9055C3200287A8A08" originalValue="wärmeren" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">waermeren</normalizedToken>
Lagen. Riedwiesen, 
<normalizedToken id="0BE45E466FEBE688834E15D777B9B5CA" originalValue="Auenwälder" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Auenwaelder</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="1958DFC33F5FAD289C74E7598D30A25A" originalValue="Gräben" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Graeben</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="95C58147317E09C0498DA99C8788D91A" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">
<emphasis id="E8BDDFEE93FE5C8E6FE747D7E08B68E0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">
Verbreitung. 
<normalizedToken id="9BA8F4E0DAA3296A6FC8289BAB4DBB1D" originalValue="Mitteleuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">Mitteleuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze:
</emphasis>
Vielleicht nur im Gebiet des Rheins. - Im Gebiet: Oberrheinische Tiefebene, Gegend des Hochrheins, Bodenseegebiet und Rheintal 
<normalizedToken id="B06E0980AAE843C7F270E04348352E71" originalValue="aufwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="330">aufwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Chur, Maschwandner Allmend.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
